<Class name="JACVersion" id="0f6658a0-63c3-4f79-8f86-2255043cdf04">
    <superclass name="JACClasses"/>
    <transient/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <abstract/>
    <text>How JACBackup works.

The JACBackupControlApp must start either through the ini file or some otherway.
It can be stopped and restarted via the Schedule form.
In SDS enviroment this must start on the secondary as well as the primary, the timerEvent only start on the 
primary and most of the userNotification registered are only done on the primary (see initBackupServerApp).
The actual backup can be done on the secondary but the journal backup can only be done on the primary.
All persistent updates done via the control app are only done in timerEvent and userNotification. 
This is because the update may be initiated from the secondary. So Schedule has 2 methods for notify 
eg setStatusNotify which raises a notify to update the status and :;setStatus which changes the sched.status
and is only called from timerEvent and userNotification.

Processing via non SDS and SDS secondary is done in the same way ie the controlApp notifies its self to do
any updates, this ensures the same code is used in both cases.</text>
    <DbClassMap file="JACBack"/>
    <Constant name="VERSION" id="00f919c9-e733-48e5-b553-22d7d648e8d5">
        <source>"1.2.4"</source>
